          <title>Torrential rains return to Southern California, prompting flash flood warnings before moving east</title>
          <description><![CDATA[The third storm in just over a week drenched Southern California and prompted some local flooding but caused no major widespread damage before heading east over the mountains and south toward Mexico’s Baja California Peninsula.]]></description>
